Matt Wagner writes and renders this wonderful story about DC's three flagship characters - Batman, Superman, and Wonder Woman - and their first meeting. Wagner gives each character a great inner monologue that explores just who they are and how they fit in the world - and, indeed, what they think of each other. A critical and commercial success, Trinity paved the way for an lengthy follow-up series in 2008. These are digital copies of the three issues thanks to Minutemen-PhD; there are copies by Zone-Empire as well but I thought these were pretty great as it is. Thanks to the scanners, and please seed and enjoy! :-)
